----|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| 0 | init | (none yet) | (none yet) | – | – | initialized |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: 0 / 0 total\n- Dimensions complete: 0 / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: 0 / 2 required\n- Overlay protocols complete: 0 / 2 applicable\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 6. TREND\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 3): []\n- New findings trend (last 3): [] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 3): []\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** none\n- **Dead-end review paths:** none\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\nIteration 1: D3 Traceability — parent vs. child status consistency, parent phase-map vs. children_ids, parent spec.md scope drift vs. five real children, retrospective stale reference.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Parent spec.md `Status: Planned` while every child says `Status: Complete` — contradiction requires adjudication.\n- Five children exist on disk but the parent spec.md phase map names only four (001-004); child 005 (`005-measured-composition-and-retrieval-facets`) is undeclared in the parent scope.\n- Program retrospective §2 lists adoption lanes as \"Planned, none built\" — stale against the per-lane implementation summaries.\n- 006-deep-alignment-and-review/alignment/ is a seeded but unrun deep-alignment pass — read-only context, not authoritative output.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagno