{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784786384383,"sessionID":"ses_07275e3ebffe5lI1k2VNcASA37","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_162128c742314dd486fa1973","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md","oldString":"## 8. WHAT WORKED\n\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)","newString":"## 8. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Reading every child spec.md `Status:` and `completion_pct:` against the parent spec.md in a single pass surfaced the cross-reference contradiction in one focused scan (iteration 1)\n- Listing the filesystem children and comparing to the parent's Phase Documentation Map row count (4 vs. 5) confirmed the undeclared 005 lane without needing any code reading (iteration 1)\n- Reading the program-level retrospective.md before any child audit made F004 (program-level stale summary) obvious from the contradiction alone (iteration 1)\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n\n- None logged yet."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -64,15 +64,15 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n \n-[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n-- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n+- Reading every child spec.md `Status:` and `completion_pct:` against the parent spec.md in a single pass surfaced the cross-reference contradiction in one focused scan (iteration 1)\n+- Listing the filesystem children and comparing to the parent's Phase Documentation Map row count (4 vs. 5) confirmed the undeclared 005 lane without needing any code reading (iteration 1)\n+- Reading the program-level retrospective.md before any child audit made F004 (program-level stale summary) obvious from the contradiction alone (iteration 1)\n \n ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n \n-[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n-- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n+- None logged yet.\n \n ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -64,15 +64,15 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n \n-[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n-- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n+- Reading every child spec.md `Status:` and `completion_pct:` against the parent spec.md in a single pass surfaced the cross-reference contradiction in one focused scan (iteration 1)\n+- Listing the filesystem children and comparing to the parent's Phase Documentation Map row count (4 vs. 5) confirmed the undeclared 005 lane without needing any code reading (iteration 1)\n+- Reading the program-level retrospective.md before any child audit made F004 (program-level stale summary) obvious from the contradiction alone (iteration 1)\n \n ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n \n-[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n-- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n+- None logged yet.\n \n ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n","additions":4,"deletions":4},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784786384379,"end":1784786384381}},"id":"prt_f8d8ef5ce001o69II7hpnBFft3","sessionID":"ses_07275e3ebffe5lI1k2VNcASA37","messageID":"msg_f8d8e7c2d001QNWDnKldgEVFml"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784786384389,"sessionID":"ses_07275e3ebffe5lI1k2VNcASA37","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_220822369c1a4a97896ced39","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md","oldString":"## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\nFocus the first iteration on **cross-packet status consistency and the parent vs. child status contradiction** under the **D3 Traceability** dimension. The parent `spec.md` records `Status: Planned` and the program retrospective lists all four adoption lanes as \"Planned\", yet every child phase folder claim `Status: Complete` with notable `completion_pct: 100`. This is the single highest-value audit angle for the lineage, and it sets the baseline for the next two iterations (correctness and security follow-up).\n\nSub-axes to read on iteration 1:\n- `spec.md` parent metadata table vs. `graph-metadata.json` children_ids vs. completion percentages.\n- `parent spec.md` §3 Files to Change (\"File Path\" mentions `004-hallmark-design-system/00[1-4]-*/`) vs. the five actual children folders (001-005).\n- `parent spec.md` §4 Open Questions (\"the four adoption lanes are specced but not yet built\") vs. child implementation summaries.\n- `retrospective.md` §2 (\"All four adoption lanes are Planned, none built\") vs. child packet completion claims.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->","newString":"## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\nFocus iteration 2 on **D1 Correctness** — verify each child claim against the actual code paths the implementation summary says it touched. The 005 lane is the priority target: its `implementation-summary.md` says `Graph metadata absent under orchestrator ownership` which is a direct conflict with the parent `graph-metadata.json` `children_ids` line that already includes 005 (so the metadata was, in fact, generated and committed). Secondary: confirm the 002-evidence-envelopes \"Create\" rows (`shared/evidence-envelopes/{owned-asset-manifest.md, motion-character-handoff.md}`) actually line up with the spec's \"Files to Change\" Create columns. Also verify the 001-surgical-fixes \"anti-slop probe count ~7-15\" is empirically accurate in `design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md`.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -104,15 +104,9 @@\n \n ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n-Focus the first iteration on **cross-packet status consistency and the parent vs. child status contradiction** under the **D3 Traceability** dimension. The parent `spec.md` records `Status: Planned` and the program retrospective lists all four adoption lanes as \"Planned\", yet every child phase folder claim `Status: Complete` with notable `completion_pct: 100`. This is the single highest-value audit angle for the lineage, and it sets the baseline for the next two iterations (correctness and security follow-up).\n-\n-Sub-axes to read on iteration 1:\n-- `spec.md` parent metadata table vs. `graph-metadata.json` children_ids vs. completion percentages.\n-- `parent spec.md` §3 Files to Change (\"File Path\" mentions `004-hallmark-design-system/00[1-4]-*/`) vs. the five actual children folders (001-005).\n-- `parent spec.md` §4 Open Questions (\"the four adoption lanes are specced but not yet built\") vs. child implementation summaries.\n-- `retrospective.md` §2 (\"All four adoption lanes are Planned, none built\") vs. child packet completion claims.\n+Focus iteration 2 on **D1 Correctness** — verify each child claim against the actual code paths the implementation summary says it touched. The 005 lane is the priority target: its `implementation-summary.md` says `Graph metadata absent under orchestrator ownership` which is a direct conflict with the parent `graph-metadata.json` `children_ids` line that already includes 005 (so the metadata was, in fact, generated and committed). Secondary: confirm the 002-evidence-envelopes \"Create\" rows (`shared/evidence-envelopes/{owned-asset-manifest.md, motion-character-handoff.md}`) actually line up with the spec's \"Files to Change\" Create columns. Also verify the 001-surgical-fixes \"anti-slop probe count ~7-15\" is empirically accurate in `design-audit/references/anti-patterns-production.md`.\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-strategy