ns | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | D3 Traceability - parent vs. child status consistency | 22 | traceability | 1/3/1 | 1.0 | complete |\n| 2 | D1 Correctness - verify child claims against code | 22 | correctness | 0/0/2 | 0.13 | complete |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: 22 / 22 total (iteration 1), 22 (iteration 2, additional code-path surfaces)\n- Dimensions complete: 2 / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: 2 / 2 required (spec_code=pass per child; checklist_evidence=pass per child)\n- Overlay protocols complete: 0 / 2 applicable (feature_catalog_code=notApplicable, playbook=notApplicable)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 6. TREND\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 2): [P0:1 P1:3 P2:1] -> [P0:1 P1:3 P2:3] [stable P0/P1; increasing P2]\n- New findings trend (last 2): [5] -> [2] [decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 2): iteration 1 corr 1/0/0/1, iteration 2 corr 1/1/0/0 (pass/partial/fail/not-applicable per protocol)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** none\n- **Dead-end review paths:** none\n- **Ruled-out direction:** Treating 005 as a \"false positive\" because the impl-summary says \"graph metadata absent\" — ruled out; the actual code paths are verified and only the impl-summary's self-description is stale.\n- **Ruled-out direction:** Treating 005 lane as an \"undocumented addition\" requiring a Plan rewrite — ruled out; spec.md `Phase | 5` + impl-summary `scope lock` note confirm intentional isolation.\n- **Ruled-out direction:** Verifying 002 Create rows by reading the implementation summary alone — insufficient; had to grep the actual code to get post-edit positions.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\nIteration 3: D4 Maintainability — does the parent spec define a refresh mechanism that would catch F001-F005 in the future? Check:\n- 005 impl-summary's \"regenerate metadata + commit scoped changes\" note (line 119).\n- Parent spec.md \"Regenerate metadata; validate --recursive\" note (`spec.md:18`).\n- Whether the parent spec's `## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS` and program retrospective's `## 2. PLANNED BUT NOT BUILT` should be regenerated as part of the implementation-record pass.\n- Whether the regeneration script exists, is documented, or is ad-hoc.\n- Security (D2) sweep will be deferred unless the parent-vs-retrospective refresh path is found to be script-driven.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- P0 F001: parent Status: Planned vs. child Status: Complete — release-blocking unless reconciled.\n- P1 F002: parent spec.md scope and Phase Map declare 4 lanes while filesystem has 5 children incl. undeclared 005 (refined: 005 is intentionally isolated but parent documentation is still stale).\n- P1 F003: parent Open Questions says lanes are specced but not yet built — stale.\n- P1 F004: program retrospective.md §2 lists 4 hallmark lanes as Planned contradicting per-packet Complete.\n- P2 F005: 006-deep-alignment-and-review/alignment is a seeded but unrun deep-alignment run.\n- P2 F006: 005 impl-summary self-contradictory about child metadata (\"absent\" but file is present).\n- P2 F007: 002-evidence-envelopes spec.md Open Questions cites pre-edit line numbers (146/490/260) but post-edit positions are 207/286.\n- Stop Policy: max-iterations — 1 iteration left; convergence math is advisory only.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0101-system-deep-loop-deep-alignment-multi-executor/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-sk-design-program/004-hallmark-design-system/review/lineages/minimax-m3/deep-review-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkme